====Usage notes====
This character is a traditional character in its own right, and as such has the third meaning cited above (‘inferior’, or a related meaning), and is read as ''ban6'' (Cantonese), ''bèn'' (Mandarin), ''bun'' (Korean), or ''hon'' (Japanese). Later, this character has been used as an abbreviation for [[體]], which it has now replaced in the [[Simplified Chinese]] and Japanese [[shinjitai]] character sets. Through this usage, the character has adopted the meanings (1 and 2) and readings (Cantonese ''tai2'', Mandarin ''tǐ'' and ''tī'', Korean ''che'', Japanese ''tei'' and ''tai'', and Vietnamese ''thể'') from [[體]].

